  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">Aaeandar Vie knows what he's talking about, but he's never pulled Hate, so he's missing some details.<br>
<br>
SW corner safe spot rules.  However, you're shafted by mobs that pop every 45 mins,and VERY VERY rarely drop anything.  You can pull towards the Maestro's area early, and then move camp into the Maestro's once it's clear.  However, there are wandering mobs (Ghasts, rats, Liches) that also repop.  Because they're wandering mobs, It's hard to judge their exact spawn time, but it seems to be about 1 hour (45 mins perhaps)<br>
<br>
Pulling hate is: Securing SW Corner, clearing wanderers, pulling nearby houses, pulling Maestro's area, clearing wanderer repops, moving to Maestro's, clearing houses, wanderer repops, then finishing the 1st floor.  Then you can pull the ashenbones, and the odd other mobs that are on the 2nd floor.<br>
<br>
To remain in the SW corner indefinitely is inefficient.<br>
<br>
